nts to have its\\n own page on the site, with the option to contact that department \\ndirectly through a web form. The form can be the same for all \\ndepartments, but they want to have it sent to a different person in each\\n case.\\n<\\/p><p>At this point you might think: let\'s just create a TV and attach \\nit to template that all departments pages use. Then simply retrieve the \\nvalue of this TV inside the fb_email_to field, instead of entering a \\nreal email address there. Unfortunately this won\'t work, because:\\n<\\/p><ul>\\n\\t<li>The fb_email_to field is expecting an email address, meaning a string containing an @<\\/li>\\n\\t<li>The form is coming from a different resource, meaning its content is already rendered when being loaded on the page<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul><p>This is where the <strong>fb_email_to_dynamic<\\/strong>\\n\\tfield comes in. We can fetch the TV containing the email address of the\\n department by sending out a snippet to go look for it. As you can see \\nunder Specifications, we can use the \\n\\t<strong>current_id<\\/strong> placeholder to look inside the resource containing the form. The snippet call could be something like this (using the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/docs.modx.pro\\/en\\/components\\/pdotools\\/parser#FastField-tags\\" target=\\"_blank\\">fastField shorthand syntax of pdoParser<\\/a>):\\n<\\/p>","field":6,"settings":[]},{"value":"[[#[[+current_id]].tv.department_email]]","lang":"html","field":13,"settings":{"label":"Example"}},{"value":"<p>Now the same form can be used on multiple different pages, with a unique email_to address for every page.<br><\\/p>","field":6,"settings":[]}]},"settings":[],"parent":78}],"fieldId":"contentblocks-field-125"}},{"heading":{"value":"[[%romanesco.patterns.specifications_title]]","fieldId":"contentblocks-field-129"},"content":{"child_layouts":[{"layout":7,"content":{"main":[{"value":"{\\n    \\"caption\\": \\"Dynamic recipient address\\",\\n    \\"name\\": \\"fb_email_to_dynamic\\",\\n    \\"d